meaningMnemonic: A "company" (会社) <kanji>member</kanji> is someone who works at a company. This is a <vocabulary>company employee</vocabulary>. There are many of these in Japan. Most of them are drunk.
readingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word, which usually means on'yomi readings from the kanji. If you know the readings of your kanji you'll know how to read this as well.
